<br>
Were they fun? No!<br>
<br>
I spent hours camping in OOT to complete my Acumen Mask quest. I spent hours camping crocs for my Runescale cloak, and I've spent hours trying to get my Heart of Fire (after hours getting the Heart of Frost). The thought of the JBoots quests gives me the fear...<br>
<br>
Has anyone out there done a quest that was interesting/fun and didn't involve sitting down for hours? Don't get me wrong, I WANT to do quests, I just want them to be interesting!<br>
<br>
Please let me know if there are any interesting quests out there I should go and do. They don't have to provide uber items (some xp would be nice!), it's just sometimes after 5 hours of quad kiting Ulthorks in EW (and whats with the resists of those Warriors?!) you need a break!<br>
<br>
Oh, btw, I'm a DE, so don't have me running around in Freeport or Qeynos!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvahrakjlorjallag.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vahrak Jlorjallag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 9:04:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Quests Fun? (not a rant!)</span><hr size=1> One of the most fun quests I have done is the Phenocryst Focus quest.  It doesn't involve hardly any camping and you get to move around to a lot of different zones.  Plus the end of the quest involves a neat battle with 3 level 52-55 giants and then some drama from all the Geniods. The reward is quite nice too.  I did the end battle with 2 groups of 51ish ppl then later for a friend we did it with one group of 58ish.<br>
Just look up the info on the quest page and have fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utarabella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tarabella</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 9:04:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Are Quests Fun? (not a rant!)</span><hr size=1> I'm enjoying doing the prayer shawl quest. Did you do the Staff of the wheel quest? Travelling to all the different zones and wondering if Invis would work  was fun, exciting and interesting. Since you're a de, you could try and do the Mystic cloak quest.. trying to not be killed by goodie type guards is always fun. Its very easy btw to notbe kos in Freeport or Qeynos (my de wizard is amaible in Qeynos, indiff in Freeport(except North). I did some quests for my alts such as the Darkforge armor and Crafted armor quests. Those were fun and gave good exp even at lvl 51. Just some suggestions. <p>Tarabella Nytesbeauty<BR>
